hauling a shovel with her,

00:38:36.170 --> 00:38:40.390
like one named Aralee ought,
with hands big as a horse's,

00:38:40.390 --> 00:38:43.010
and who, like one
named Aralee ought,

00:38:43.010 --> 00:38:46.830
will laugh time to time til
the juice runs from her nose.

00:38:46.830 --> 00:38:49.960
Oh, thank you for the
way a small thing's wail

00:38:49.960 --> 00:38:52.530
makes the milk or
what once was milk

00:38:52.530 --> 00:38:57.440
in us gather into horses
huckle-buckling across a field.

00:38:57.440 --> 00:39:01.860
And thank you friends, when last
spring the hyacinth bells rang

00:39:01.860 --> 00:39:04.920
and the crocuses flaunted
their upturned skirts,

00:39:04.920 --> 00:39:07.590
and a quiet roved
the beehive which

00:39:07.590 --> 00:39:09.570
when I entered were
snugged two or three

00:39:09.570 --> 00:39:13.630
dead fist-sized clutches
of bees between the frames,

00:39:13.630 --> 00:39:17.510
almost clinging to one another,
this one's tiny head pushed

00:39:17.510 --> 00:39:20.840
into another's tiny wings,
one's forelegs resting

00:39:20.840 --> 00:39:23.310
on another's face,
the translucent paper

00:39:23.310 --> 00:39:25.960
of their wings fluttering
beneath my breath

00:39:25.960 --> 00:39:30.670
and when a few dropped to
the frames beneath, honey.

00:39:30.670 --> 00:39:35.280
And after falling down to cry,
everything's glacial shine.

00:39:35.280 --> 00:39:38.120
And thank you, too.

00:39:38.120 --> 00:39:42.380
And thanks for the corduroy
couch I have put you on.

00:39:42.380 --> 00:39:44.320
Put your feet up.

00:39:44.320 --> 00:39:48.290
Here's a blanket, a
pillow, dear ones,

00:39:48.290 --> 00:39:51.210
for I think this is
going to be long.

00:39:51.210 --> 00:39:54.020
I can't stop my
gratitude, which includes,

00:39:54.020 --> 00:39:58.050
dear reader, you, for
staying here with me,

00:39:58.050 --> 00:40:01.690
for removing the lips
just so as I speak.

00:40:01.690 --> 00:40:03.560
Here is a cup of tea.

00:40:03.560 --> 00:40:06.170
I've spooned honey into it.

00:40:06.170 --> 00:40:09.860
And thank you the tiny bee's
shadow perusing these words

00:40:09.860 --> 00:40:13.380
as I write them and the way
my love talks quietly when

00:40:13.380 --> 00:40:15.230
in the hive, so
quietly, in fact,

00:40:15.230 --> 00:40:19.240
you cannot hear her voice, but
only notice barely her lips

00:40:19.240 --> 00:40:21.660
moving in conversation.

00:40:21.660 --> 00:40:23.810
Thank you what does
not scare her in me,

00:40:23.810 --> 00:40:25.830
but makes her reach my way.

00:40:25.830 --> 00:40:28.440
Thank you the love she
is which hurts sometimes.

00:40:28.440 --> 00:40:32.440
And the time she misremembered
elephants in one of my poems,

00:40:32.440 --> 00:40:37.430
which here they come, garlanded
with morning glory and wisteria

00:40:37.430 --> 00:40:41.110
blooms, trombones all the
way down to the river.

00:40:41.110 --> 00:40:43.850
Thank you the quiet in
which the river bends around

00:40:43.850 --> 00:40:47.570
the elephant's solemn trunk,
polishing stones, floating

00:40:47.570 --> 00:40:51.860
on its gentle back, the flock
of geese flying overhead.

00:40:51.860 --> 00:40:54.510
And to the quick and
gentle flocking of men

00:40:54.510 --> 00:40:57.910
to the old lady falling down
on the corner of Fairmount

00:40:57.910 --> 00:41:01.620
and 18th, holding patiently
with the softest parts

00:41:01.620 --> 00:41:05.350
of their hands her
cane and purple hat,

00:41:05.350 --> 00:41:07.185
gathering for her the
contents of her purse

00:41:07.185 --> 00:41:10.800
and touching her
shoulder and elbow.

00:41:10.800 --> 00:41:13.720
Thank you the cockeyed
court on which

00:41:13.720 --> 00:41:15.720
in a half-court
three on three, we

00:41:15.720 --> 00:41:19.150
oldheads made of some
runny-nosed kids a shambles,

00:41:19.150 --> 00:41:22.420
and the 61-year-old--
the 61-year-old

00:41:22.420 --> 00:41:25.030
after flipping a reverse
lay-up off a back door cut

00:41:25.030 --> 00:41:28.870
from my no-look pass to seal
the game ripped off his shirt

00:41:28.870 --> 00:41:31.130
and threw punches at the
gods and hollered at the kids

00:41:31.130 --> 00:41:36.040
to admire the pacemaker's scar
grinning across his chest.

00:41:36.040 --> 00:41:39.860
Thank you the glad accordian's
wheeze in the chest.

00:41:39.860 --> 00:41:41.940
Thank you the bagpipes.

00:41:41.940 --> 00:41:44.630
Thank you to the woman
barefoot in the gaudy dress

00:41:44.630 --> 00:41:47.230
for stopping her car in
the middle of the road

00:41:47.230 --> 00:41:51.250
and the tractor trailer behind
her, and the van behind it,

00:41:51.250 --> 00:41:54.070
whisking a turtle off the road.

00:41:54.070 --> 00:41:56.340
Thank you god of gaudy.

00:41:56.340 --> 00:41:58.270
Thank you paisley panties.

00:41:58.270 --> 00:42:01.820
Thank you the organ up my dress.

00:42:01.820 --> 00:42:03.690
Thank you the sheer
dress you wore

00:42:03.690 --> 00:42:06.970
kneeling in my dream
at the creek's edge

00:42:06.970 --> 00:42:09.270
and the light
swimming through it.

00:42:09.270 --> 00:42:14.120
The koi kissing halos into the
glassy air, the room in my mind

00:42:14.120 --> 00:42:16.410
with the blinds
drawn where we nearly

00:42:16.410 --> 00:42:20.670
injure each other crawling into
the shawl of the other's body.

00:42:20.670 --> 00:42:23.500
Thank you when I
just say it plain--

00:42:23.500 --> 00:42:26.160
we fuck each other dumb.

00:42:26.160 --> 00:42:31.340
And you, again, you,
for the true kindness

00:42:31.340 --> 00:42:34.350
it has been for you to remain
awake with me like this,

00:42:34.350 --> 00:42:38.160
nodding time to time and making
that little noise that I take

00:42:38.160 --> 00:42:44.240
to mean yes, or, I understand,
or, please go on, but not

00:42:44.240 --> 00:42:48.770
too long, or why are you
spitting so much, or easy

00:42:48.770 --> 00:42:51.570
Tiger, hands to yourself.

00:42:51.570 --> 00:42:53.950
I am excitable.

00:42:53.950 --> 00:42:56.560
I am sorry.

00:42:56.560 --> 00:42:58.090
I am grateful.

00:42:58.090 --> 00:43:01.070
I just want us to be
friends now, forever.

00:43:01.070 --> 00:43:03.640
Take this bowl of
blackberries from the garden.

00:43:03.640 --> 00:43:05.520
The sun has made them warm.

00:43:05.520 --> 00:43:07.300
I picked them just for you.

00:43:07.300 --> 00:43:12.390
I promise, I will try to
stay on my side of the couch.

00:43:12.390 --> 00:43:14.800
And thank you the baggie
of dreadlocks I found

00:43:14.800 --> 00:43:17.160
in the drawer while washing
and folding the clothes

00:43:17.160 --> 00:43:20.800
of our murdered friend, the
photo in which his arm slung

00:43:20.800 --> 00:43:24.820
around the sign to the 'trail
of silences.' Thank you the way

00:43:24.820 --> 00:43:28.670
before he died, he held
his hands open to us,

00:43:28.670 --> 00:43:31.990
for coming back in a waft
of incense or in the shape

00:43:31.990 --> 00:43:36.140
of a boy in another city looking
from between his mother's legs,

00:43:36.140 --> 00:43:40.150
or disappearing into the stacks
after brushing by, for moseying

00:43:40.150 --> 00:43:44.320
back in dreams where, seeing us
lost and scared he put his hand

00:43:44.320 --> 00:43:49.250
on our shoulders and pointed
us to the temple across town.

00:43:49.250 --> 00:43:51.700
And thank you to the
man all night long

00:43:51.700 --> 00:43:54.810
hosing a mist on his
early-bloomed peach tree

00:43:54.810 --> 00:43:59.360
so that the hard frost not waste
the crop, the ice in his beard

00:43:59.360 --> 00:44:02.420
and the ghosts lifting from
him when the warming sun

00:44:02.420 --> 00:44:04.340
told him sleep now.

00:44:04.340 --> 00:44:06.460
Thank you the
ancestor who loved you

00:44:06.460 --> 00:44:10.060
before she knew you by
smuggling seeds into her braid

00:44:10.060 --> 00:44:13.540
for the long journey, who
loved you before he knew you

00:44:13.540 --> 00:44:16.460
by putting a walnut tree in
the ground, who loved you

00:44:16.460 --> 00:44:19.370
before she knew you by
not slaughtering the land.

00:44:19.370 --> 00:44:22.930
Thank you who did not bulldoze
the ancient grove of dates

00:44:22.930 --> 00:44:26.010
and olives, who sailed
his keys into the ocean

00:44:26.010 --> 00:44:29.360
and walked softly home, who
did not fire, who did not

00:44:29.360 --> 00:44:31.980
plunge the head into the
toilet, who said stop,

00:44:31.980 --> 00:44:35.630
don't do that, who lifted
some broken someone up,

00:44:35.630 --> 00:44:39.390
who volunteered the way a plant
birthed of the receding plant

00:44:39.390 --> 00:44:42.700
is called a volunteer, like
the plum tree that marched

00:44:42.700 --> 00:44:44.780
beside the raised
bed in my garden,

00:44:44.780 --> 00:44:46.470
like the arugula
that marched itself

00:44:46.470 --> 00:44:50.265
between the blueberries, nary
a bayonette, nary an army, nary

00:44:50.265 --> 00:44:51.010
a nation,

00:44:51.010 --> 00:44:54.230
which usage of the word
volunteer familiar to gardeners

00:44:54.230 --> 00:44:57.870
the wide world made my
pal should 'Oh!' and dance

00:44:57.870 --> 00:45:01.100
and plunge his knuckles into the
luscious soil before gobbling

00:45:01.100 --> 00:45:03.820
two strawberries and digging
a song from his guitar made

00:45:03.820 --> 00:45:06.350
of wood from a tree
someone planted.

00:45:06.350 --> 00:45:07.180
Thank you.

00:45:07.180 --> 00:45:10.830
Thank you zinna, and gooseberry,
rudbeckia, and pawpaw,

00:45:10.830 --> 00:45:14.210
Ashmead's kernel, cockscomb,
and scarlet runner, feverfew

00:45:14.210 --> 00:45:15.230
and lemonblam.

00:45:15.230 --> 00:45:17.510
Thank you knitbone and
sweetgrass and sunchoke

00:45:17.510 --> 00:45:22.710
and false indigo whose petals
stammered apart by bumblebees

00:45:22.710 --> 00:45:25.095
good lord please
give me a minute.

00:45:28.560 --> 00:45:31.010
And moonglow and
catkin and crookneck

00:45:31.010 --> 00:45:34.370
and painted tongue and
seedpod and johnny jump-up.

00:45:34.370 --> 00:45:37.890
Thank you what in us rackets
glad what gladrackets us.

00:45:37.890 --> 00:45:40.940
And thank you too, this
knuckleheaded heart,

00:45:40.940 --> 00:45:43.820
this pelican heart,
this gap-toothed heart

00:45:43.820 --> 00:45:46.690
flinging open its
gaudy maw to the sky,

00:45:46.690 --> 00:45:51.110
oh clumsy, oh bumblefucked,
oh giddy, oh dumbstruck,

00:45:51.110 --> 00:45:54.065
oh rickshaw, oh goat
twisting its head at me

00:45:54.065 --> 00:45:58.320
from my peach tree's highest
branch, balanced impossibly

00:45:58.320 --> 00:46:00.810
gobbling the last
fruit, its tongue

00:46:00.810 --> 00:46:04.610
working like an engine, a
lone sweet drop tumbling

00:46:04.610 --> 00:46:08.470
by some a miracle into my
mouth like the smell of someone

00:46:08.470 --> 00:46:11.940
I've loved, heart like
an elephant screaming

00:46:11.940 --> 00:46:16.170
at the bones of its dead, heart
like a lady on the bus dressed

00:46:16.170 --> 00:46:20.700
head to toe in gold, the sun
shivering her shiny boots,

00:46:20.700 --> 00:46:23.300
singing Erykah Badu
to herself leaning

00:46:23.300 --> 00:46:25.430
her head against the window.

00:46:25.430 --> 00:46:28.600
And thank you the way one time
my father came back in a dream

00:46:28.600 --> 00:46:31.720
by plucking the two cables
beneath my chin like a bass

00:46:31.720 --> 00:46:34.530
fiddle's strings and played
me until I woke singing.

00:46:34.530 --> 00:46:38.530
No kidding, I was singing
and smiling, thank you.

00:46:38.530 --> 00:46:41.170
Thank you, stumbling into the
garden where the Juneberry's

00:46:41.170 --> 00:46:44.760
flowers had burst open like
the bells of French horns,

00:46:44.760 --> 00:46:46.900
the lily my mother
and I planted oozed

00:46:46.900 --> 00:46:51.030
into the air, the
bazillion ants labored

00:46:51.030 --> 00:46:53.130
in their earthen
workshops below,

00:46:53.130 --> 00:46:56.540
the collared greens waved in the
wind like the sales of ships,

00:46:56.540 --> 00:47:00.660
and the wasps swam in the
mint bloom's viscous swill.

00:47:00.660 --> 00:47:08.500
And you, again you, for
hanging tight, friends.

00:47:08.500 --> 00:47:12.750
I know I can be long
winded sometimes.

00:47:12.750 --> 00:47:15.980
I want so badly to rub
the sponge of gratitude

00:47:15.980 --> 00:47:24.700
over every thing, including
you, which is awkward.

00:47:24.700 --> 00:47:27.575
The little soap running
into your hoodie

00:47:27.575 --> 00:47:30.410
or down your collar.

00:47:30.410 --> 00:47:33.460
Soon it will be
over, which is what

00:47:33.460 --> 00:47:37.940
the little girl in my dream
said, holding my hand,

00:47:37.940 --> 00:47:40.250
pointing at the
rolling sea and the sky

00:47:40.250 --> 00:47:42.850
hurtling our way like so
many buffalo, who said,

00:47:42.850 --> 00:47:48.450
it's much worse than
you think, and sooner.

00:47:48.450 --> 00:47:53.480
To whom I said, no duh
child in my dreams.

00:47:53.480 --> 00:47:55.530
What do you think this
singing and shuddering

00:47:55.530 --> 00:47:58.970
is, what this screaming and
reaching and dancing and crying

00:47:58.970 --> 00:48:03.270
is, other than loving what
every second goes away?

00:48:03.270 --> 00:48:05.946
Goodbye, I mean to say.

00:48:05.946 --> 00:48:07.600
And thank you.

00:48:07.600 --> 00:48:09.400
Every day."

00:48:09.400 --> 00:48:10.950
Thank you.

